description.en: Models key tourism elements such as attractions, events, hotels, restaurants, and transport in a structured way. It facilitates the analysis and reuse of tourism knowledge in urban environments for smart applications.

comments.en: Ontology that models tourism-related data such as cities, events, hotels, and transport for smart recommendations.

comment.en: A place where meals are prepared and served to customers.

comment.undefined: A building or institution that houses and displays artifacts and exhibitions.

comment.en: A general concept that represents any entity that can be identified by a name, such as cities, events, attractions, hotels, or restaurants. Used to unify domain usage of the name data property.
A hotel with a high evaluation based on user feedback or rating metrics.
A hotel located within an urban area.
Public or private transportation via buses.
An urban area that can host events, services, and attractions.
A scheduled occasion such as a concert, festival, or sports competition.
An abstract class representing any entity that can receive a rating or evaluation, such as hotels, restaurants or attractions.

comment.undefined: A place of historical significance, such as a monument or landmark.

comment.en: A restaurant with a high user rating or recognized quality.
An entity that is classified by type, such as restaurants or attractions.
A restaurant that serves quick and inexpensive meals.
Recommended Hotel
A high-quality restaurant offering refined cuisine.
A category encompassing means of travel or transit.
A high-end hotel offering premium services and accommodations.
A natural site or feature of interest to visitors, such as mountains or parks.
A city that serves as the capital of a country or region.
A city that organizes at least one event.
A commercial establishment offering lodging and other services to travelers.
A competitive or recreational sporting event.

comment.undefined: A multi-performance event dedicated to musical entertainment.
A hotel that offers 5-star service at a price lower than 100€ per night.

comment.en: A form of transportation using trains or railways.
CityWithTransport
A mode of transportation via aircraft, such as planes or helicopters.
An event related to cultural expression, tradition, or art.
A place or feature that attracts tourists or visitors
Indicates the geographic location of an entity, typically linking a tourism service or event to the city where it takes place.
The average price associated with the item (for example, a typical selling price).
The name or title of the item.
The geographic location or address of the item.
The type or category of a hotel (e.g., resort, hostel, bed-and-breakfast).
The type of cuisine offered (e.g., Italian, Chinese).
Indicates the city or organization responsible for organizing a given event.
A general type or category of the item.
Has transport
The price per night (for example, a nightly rate for lodging).
The company or organization associated with the item (e.g., its provider or organizer).
Relates an entity to the city where it is geographically situated
A rating or evaluation score for the item (often based on user reviews or quality).
The average cost associated with the item or service.
The star rating of an accommodation (e.g., a 5-star rating).
Indicates that a city is responsible for organizing a given event.
A date associated with the item (e.g., the date on which an event occurs).
